  "bio_raw": "Neha Ghose has worked as a part time lecturer and an English tutor before. She has completed her BA and MA at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB). She has also completed her 2\nnd\nMA from University of Sussex, UK. In addition to her teaching roles, Neha also gained research experience as a Research Intern at the Center for Critical and Qualitative Studies, ULAB (CQS) and as a Data Transcriber at the Center for Sustainable Development, ULAB (CSD). Currently, she is teaching as a Lecturer in the Department of English and Humanities at ULAB and also working as an Advisor to ULAB English Zone.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Literary and Media Representation, Popular Culture, Intersectionality, Cultural Studies, Audience Studies."
  ],
  "education": [
